quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  39,57,"Or (so that no soul) may say, “If Allah had shown me the right path, I would then be among the pious!”"
  39,58,"Or (so that no soul) may say when it beholds the punishment, “If only I may be sent back, so that I may do good deeds!”"
  39,59,"It will be said to him, “Surely yes, why not?* My signs did come to you, so you denied them and you were haughty and you were a disbeliever.” (They will be mocked at.)"
  39,60,"And you will see on the Day of Resurrection the fabricators of lies against Allah, with their faces blackened; is not the destination of the haughty in hell?"
  39,61,"And Allah will rescue the pious, to their place of salvation; neither will the punishment touch them, nor shall they grieve."
  39,62,"Allah is Creator of all things; and He only is the Controller of all things."
  39,63,"For Him only are the keys of the heavens and the earth; and those who denied the signs of Allah – it is they who are the losers."
  39,64,"Say (O dear Prophet Mohammed – peace and blessings be upon him) “So do you instruct me to worship (deities) other than Allah? You ignorant fools!”"
  39,65,"And it was indeed revealed to you and to those before you; that, “O listener! If you ascribe a partner to Allah, all your deeds will go to waste and you will surely be a loser.”"
  39,66,"But rather worship only Allah, and be among the thankful!"
  39,67,"And they did not realise the importance of Allah as was His right; and on the Day of Resurrection, He will compress the lands and the heavens will be rolled up by His power; Purity and Supremacy are to Him, from all what they ascribe as partners."
